**Title:** Slow Loading Time for JavaScript Files During Initial Page Load Under 3G Conditions

**Summary:**  
When accessing the site [demo.benefiti.rs](http://demo.benefiti.rs) under 3G network conditions, the JavaScript files load significantly slower than expected. This leads to a delayed content display and increases the time to page interactivity.

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Open Chrome browser   
2. Open the application: [https://demo.benefiti.rs/\#/](https://demo.benefiti.rs/#/).  
3. Open **Developer Tools** (press **F12**), or right-clicking on the page and selecting **"Inspect"**.  
4. Click on the **Network** tab.  
5. Select the **Slow 3G** option from the **Throttling** dropdown.  
6. Perform a **Hard reload** of the page (press **Ctrl \+ Shift \+ R**).  
   

**Expected Result:**  
All script files should load within a reasonable timeframe (10-15 seconds) even under 3G conditions.

**Actual Result:**  
The script.js file takes **1.6 minutes** to fully load and execute.

**Environment:**OS Windows 11Pro,Browser:Chrome v117, Network conditions: 3G slow (Throttle u Network tab-u)

**Bug ID:** 002

**Title:** High Total Blocking Time and Slow User Interaction Response on mobile view

**Summary:**  
The application experiences significant performance degradation in the mobile view, with a high Total Blocking Time (TBT) of 18,410 ms and a slow Interaction to Next Paint (INP) of 6,350 ms. This was observed during testing using Lighthouse in Google Chrome's Incognito mode. The issue causes noticeable delays in responsiveness and overall interaction with the application.

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Open **Google Chrome** in **Incognito Mode**.  
2. Navigate to the page [https://demo.benefiti.rs/\#/](https://demo.benefiti.rs/#/).  
3. Open **Chrome Developer Tools** by pressing `F12` .  
4. Click on the **Network** tab.  
5. Select the **Slow 3G** option from the **Throttling** dropdown.  
6. Select the **Lighthouse** tab from the available tools.  
7. Choose the **Mobile** configuration.
8. Click on **Generate Report**.

**Expected Result:**
The Total Blocking Time (TBT) should  be under 300 ms to provide smooth user interactions .Interaction to Next Paint (INP) should be under 200 ms, so that users can interact with the page without noticeable delays.

**Actual Result:**
The Total Blocking Time (TBT) is **18,410 ms**, far exceeding acceptable limits, causing long delays in responding to user actions. The Interaction to Next Paint (INP) is **6,350 ms.**

**Test Environment:** OS Windows 11Pro, Device Emulation: iPhone 14 Pro Max  using Chrome Developer Tools, Browser: Chrome v117, Mode:Incognito, Network Throttling: 3G (for simulating slower mobile network),Tools: Lighthouse (Performance tab) in Chrome DevTools.
